               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus contract from Egypt made by Severus with the son of the deceased Serenus. Severus swears by God Almighty. The signature is in the form of a cross. Witnesses are Kyrillos and David. Verso has a documentary text in Coptic (P.Duk.inv. 487 V)</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 12.3 x 18.0 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">11 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers on the recto; written along the fibers on the verso in a different hand</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 1 cm.; lower margin of 1.5 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 487 R was formerly P.Miss. 53 R</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="cop">In Coptic</textLang>
